========================================================================
LESSONS LEARNED — first fresh-pod bootstrap of `main` (2026-05-30)
========================================================================
Pod: RunPod A100-SXM4-80GB, /workspace = MooseFS (mfs#us-md-1.runpod.net:9421),
/root = 30 GB overlay. System CUDA (nvcc) 12.8; driver CUDA 13.0. Python 3.12.3.

WHAT BROKE (full writeup: FRICTION.md F-013):
  1. bootstrap.sh `uv pip install mamba_ssm --no-build-isolation` silently
     upgraded torch 2.5.1+cu121 -> 2.12.0+cu130 (mamba_ssm 2.3.2.post1
     hard-requires torch==2.12). --no-build-isolation does NOT stop runtime
     dependency resolution. Result: causal_conv1d source build failed the
     torch CUDA-version check (cu130 vs nvcc 12.8), and mamba's compiled .so
     was ABI-broken.
  2. After adding --no-deps, mamba latest (2.3.2.post1) disagreed with
     requirements.txt's resolve (2.3.1) -> uv tried to rebuild 2.3.1 under
     build isolation -> pulled cu13 torch + cublas into a temp env -> filled
     the 30 GB /root overlay (os error 28).

FIX (committed to bootstrap.sh + requirements.txt):
  - Pin mamba_ssm==2.3.1 and causal_conv1d==1.6.2.post1 in BOTH files.
  - Install them --no-build-isolation --no-deps (reuse the cu121 torch).
  - Add einops to Step 2 (real mamba_ssm runtime dep that --no-deps skips).

THROUGHPUT SAMPLES (local overlay disk, UV_CACHE_DIR=/root/uv-cache):
  - torch 2.5.1+cu121 + 22 CUDA wheels:        download-bound, ~20 s prepare
  - causal_conv1d 1.6.2.post1 from source:     8m26s (multi-arch nvcc compile)
  - mamba_ssm 2.3.1 from source:               8m47s (multi-arch nvcc compile)
  - requirements.txt (43 pure-Python wheels):  ~2 s prepare, <1 s install
  NOTE: runpod-setup.md § 2's "bootstrap ~2 s / requirements ~10 s" assumes
  prebuilt wheels; from-source CUDA builds dominate (~17 min total here).

DISK: `uv cache clean` reclaimed 19.2 GiB of dead cu12+cu13 wheels left by the
